  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA311-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu alar kūṟappaṭṭu āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷait tōḻi āṟṟuvittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante gave strength to HER who was unable to bear it when being talked about by gossip.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA311">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            peyiṉē</l>
<l>            viṭumā ṉuḻaiyiṉ veṟuppat tōṉṟi</l>
<l>            yiruṅkatir nelliṉ yāṇa raḵtē</l>
<l>            vaṟappiṉ</l>
<l>            mānīr muṇṭakan tāayc cēṟupularn</l>
<l>            tiruṅkaḻic ceṟuviṉ veḷḷuppu viḷaiyu</l>
<l>            maḻiyā marapiṉam mūtūr naṉṟē</l>
<l>            koḻumīṉ cuṭupukai maṟukiṉuṇ mayaṅkic</l>
<l>            ciṟuvī ñāḻaṟ ṟuṟaiyumā riṉitē</l>
<l>            yoṉṟē tōḻinam kāṉalatu paḻiyē</l>
<l>            karuṅkōṭṭup puṉṉai malariṟṟā tarunti</l>
<l>            yiruṅkaḷip piraca mūtavavar</l>
<l>            neṭuntē riṉṉoli kēṭṭalō varitē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent4">If it rains,</l>
<l>it [has] the yield of big-eared rice,</l>
<l rend="indent">an abundance of deer let loose appearing.</l>
<l rend="indent4">It if gets dry,</l>
<l rend="indent">when white salt ripens in the fields of the dark backwaters,</l>
<l rend="indent">mud dried, Muṇṭakam[-blossoms] spread by the great water,</l>
<l>our old village of unchanging custom [is] good.</l>
<l>Pleasing [is] also the ghat with small-blossomed Ñāḻal trees,</l>
<l rend="indent">the inside of streets diffused with the glowing smoke of rich fish.</l>
<l>One only, friend, [is] the blame of our seashore grove.</l>
<l>As for hearing the sweet sound of his long chariot,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the bees<note place="foot">Here the combination with <term xml:lang="ta">ūta</term> induces us to take <term xml:lang="ta">piracam</term> to mean "bee" here, not the usual "honeycomb".</note> are filling themselves on great nectar, eating</l>
<l rend="indent">the pollen from the blossoms of the black-branched Puṉṉai tree,</l>
<l rend="indent4">that [is] difficult.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
